title: Documentation - Vertex AI Optical Character Recognition API
abstract:
# Documentation - Vertex AI Optical Character Recognition API
This is the gRPC API reference for the Optical Character Recognition pre-trained API that is included with   Vertex AI on Google Distributed Cloud Hosted (GDCH). Use this guide to programmatically detect text in files and images.
content:
## Service: Optical Character Recognition (OCR)The Service name `` is required to create RPC client stubs. For more information, see [View   Vertex AI service statuses and endpoints](/distributed-cloud/hosted/docs/latest/gdch/application/ao-user/vertex-ai-api-status) OCR and Optical Character Recognition are not formal product names, so don't appear in _product_names.html. However, the PM would like to treat it as a product name for GDCH with title-case in the long form. These variables enforce that for GDCH. 
## google.cloud.vision.v1.ImageAnnotator
| Methods    | Methods.1                 |
|:--------------------|:---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| BatchAnnotateFiles | Service that performs image detection and annotation for a batch of files. |
| BatchAnnotateImages | Run image detection and annotation for a batch of images.     |
